### P-2: Industry Cards — Hover Effects Don't Translate to Mobile

**Problem:** The `OfferAndIndustrySection` cards have rich hover states: `-translate-y-2`, shadow changes, border color shifts, scale changes on non-hovered cards (`opacity-80 scale-[0.98]`), icon scale-up, gradient top-bar reveal. **None of this works on mobile.** Touch devices don't have hover. The cards look static and flat compared to their desktop versions.

**Recommended approach:** Replace hover interactions with scroll-triggered and tap-triggered states:

1. **On scroll into view:** Stagger the card entrance with slight scale (0.95 → 1.0) + opacity. Already partially done.

2. **Active/expanded state on tap:** When user taps a card on mobile, expand it slightly to reveal the hidden outcome quote (currently `hidden md:flex`). This turns the cards into **tap-to-expand** interactive elements.

```
Collapsed (default):
┌────────────────────────┐
│ 🏗️ Walkthrough-Ready    │
│ General Contractors     │
│ 200+ closeouts          │
│ [pain point text]       │
│ Best for: Final Walk... │
│ [Discuss Your Project →]│
│            ▼ More       │
└────────────────────────┘

Expanded (on tap):
┌────────────────────────┐
│ 🏗️ Walkthrough-Ready    │
│ General Contractors     │
│ 200+ closeouts          │
│ [pain point text]       │
│ ─────────────────────── │
│ Best for:               │
│ • Final Walkthroughs    │
│ • Multi-Trade Closeouts │
│ • Schedule-Sensitive    │
│ ─────────────────────── │
│ "A&A helps tighten the  │
│  final presentation..." │
│ [Discuss Your Project →]│
└────────────────────────┘
```

**Implementation:**
```tsx
const [expandedIndex, setExpandedIndex] = useState<number | null>(null);

// On the card:
onClick={() => setExpandedIndex(expandedIndex === index ? null : index)}

// Show outcome quote when expanded (mobile only):
<div className={`overflow-hidden transition-all duration-300 md:flex ${
  expandedIndex === index ? "max-h-40 opacity-100 mt-4" : "max-h-0 opacity-0"
} md:max-h-none md:opacity-100`}>
  {/* outcome quote content */}
</div>
```

**Impact:** Recovers hidden content, adds interactivity, replaces non-functional hover states. Mobile users get the full value proposition per industry without the cards being permanently expanded (which would add ~400px of scroll).

**Effort:** Small-Medium (3–4 hours).

