### P-5: Image Loading Strategy — Blur Placeholder

**Problem:** Below-fold images (service spread ×5, about section, careers, quote panel, before/after) load without placeholders. On slow mobile connections, users see either a blank space or a sudden pop-in. Next.js Image supports `placeholder="blur"` with `blurDataURL` but it's not used anywhere.

**Recommended approach:** Add blur placeholders to all below-fold images:

```tsx
<Image
  src={service.image}
  alt="..."
  fill
  quality={68}
  placeholder="blur"
  blurDataURL="data:image/jpeg;base64,/9j/4AAQSkZJRgABAQAAAQABAAD/2wBDA..."
  sizes="(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 58vw"
  className="object-cover"
/>
```

For generating blur data URLs, either:
- Use `plaiceholder` package at build time
- Or use a tiny 8×8 dominant-color JPEG as a static placeholder

**Impact:** Eliminates content pop-in, creates a smooth loading experience, improves perceived performance significantly on mobile. This is standard on every production Next.js site.

**Effort:** Small-Medium (2–3 hours including generating blur data for ~10 images).

