## Category 1: Dead Configuration & Unused Theme Extensions

### DC-1: `tailwind.config.ts` — Extensive Unused Custom Theme

The config defines custom extensions that are **never referenced** in any component:

| Config Section | Defined Values | Used in Components? |
|---|---|---|
| `colors.navy`, `colors.gold`, `colors.royal`, `colors.warm`, `colors.dark-panel` | 10+ custom colors | **No** — all components use literal hex: `bg-[#0A1628]`, `text-[#C9A94E]`, etc. |
| `fontSize.micro`, `fontSize.kicker` | 2 custom sizes | **No** — components use `text-[10px]`, `text-[11px]` |
| `letterSpacing.kicker`, `.wide`, `.wider`, `.label`, `.chips` | 5 custom values | **No** — components use `tracking-[0.18em]`, `tracking-[0.24em]` |
| `borderRadius.panel`, `.card` | 2 custom values | **No** — components use `rounded-3xl`, `rounded-2xl` |
| `boxShadow.panel-soft`, `.panel-dark`, `.hero-glow`, `.cta-blue` | 4 custom shadows | **No** — components use `shadow-[0_28px_90px_...]` inline |
| `backgroundImage.dot-pattern`, `.gold-radial` | 2 custom BGs | **No** — components use inline `style={{ backgroundImage: "..." }}` |
| `backgroundSize.dots`, `.dots-sm`, `.dots-lg` | 3 custom sizes | **No** |
| `animation.fade-up`, `.ken-burns`, `.bounce-subtle` | 3 custom animations | **No** — components use inline `style={{ animation: "..." }}` |

**Impact:** Not a bundle issue (Tailwind tree-shakes unused utilities), but it's a **maintenance trap**. New developers will assume these tokens are the design system and try to use them, only to find every component uses hardcoded values instead.

**Recommendation for Gemini:**

> **Option A (Clean):** Remove all unused extensions from `tailwind.config.ts`. Keep only `fontFamily.serif` which IS used via `font-serif` class.
>
> **Option B (Adopt):** Migrate components to use the defined tokens. Replace `bg-[#0A1628]` with `bg-navy`, `text-[#C9A94E]` with `text-gold`, etc. across all files. This is a larger effort but creates a real design system.
>
> **Recommended: Option A now, Option B as post-launch tech debt.** The config cleanup is safe and fast. Token adoption is a refactor that should happen when the design system stabilizes.

