### R-4: BeforeAfterSlider — Global Event Listeners Always Active

```tsx
useEffect(() => {
  const onMouseMove = (e: MouseEvent) => onMove(e.clientX);
  const onTouchMove = (e: TouchEvent) => { ... };
  const onEnd = () => { ... };

  // These are ALWAYS registered while component is mounted:
  window.addEventListener("mousemove", onMouseMove);
  window.addEventListener("mouseup", onEnd);
  window.addEventListener("touchmove", onTouchMove, { passive: true });
  window.addEventListener("touchend", onEnd);
  // ...
```

Four global listeners fire on every mouse/touch event even when the user isn't dragging. The `isDraggingRef` check exits early, but the event handler functions still execute and the browser still dispatches events.

**Fix:** Only attach listeners when drag starts, detach on end:

```tsx
const startDrag = useCallback((clientX: number) => {
  isDraggingRef.current = true;
  setIsDragging(true);
  updatePosition(clientX);

  const onMouseMove = (e: MouseEvent) => updatePosition(e.clientX);
  const onTouchMove = (e: TouchEvent) => {
    const touch = e.touches[0];
    if (touch) updatePosition(touch.clientX);
  };
  const onEnd = () => {
    isDraggingRef.current = false;
    setIsDragging(false);
    window.removeEventListener("mousemove", onMouseMove);
    window.removeEventListener("mouseup", onEnd);
    window.removeEventListener("touchmove", onTouchMove);
    window.removeEventListener("touchend", onEnd);
  };

  window.addEventListener("mousemove", onMouseMove);
  window.addEventListener("mouseup", onEnd);
  window.addEventListener("touchmove", onTouchMove, { passive: true });
  window.addEventListener("touchend", onEnd);
}, [updatePosition]);
```

Remove the existing always-on `useEffect` for global listeners.

**Impact:** Eliminates 4 continuous global event listeners. Meaningful on mobile where touch events fire at 60fps during any scroll.

