### MF-3: ExitIntentOverlay — Never Triggers on Mobile

The `ExitIntentOverlay` only listens for `mouseleave` events, which don't fire on mobile. The overlay will **never show** to mobile users — ~60-70% of traffic sees nothing.

**Recommendation:** Add a mobile-specific trigger. The safest mobile exit intent patterns:

```tsx
// Add to the existing useEffect:

// Mobile: trigger on rapid scroll-up (user heading back to top = leaving intent)
const handleScroll = () => {
  if (window.scrollY > 600) {
    hasScrolledRef.current = true;
  }
  
  // Mobile exit intent: rapid upward scroll
  if (
    !hasShownRef.current &&
    hasScrolledRef.current &&
    timeOnPageRef.current > 10_000 &&
    !sessionStorage.getItem("aa_exit_intent_shown")
  ) {
    const scrollDelta = window.scrollY - lastScrollY.current;
    if (scrollDelta < -200) { // Fast upward scroll
      hasShownRef.current = true;
      sessionStorage.setItem("aa_exit_intent_shown", "1");
      setIsVisible(true);
    }
  }
  lastScrollY.current = window.scrollY;
};
```

**Alternatively**, if mobile exit intent is intentionally disabled (it can feel intrusive), add a comment documenting the decision so future developers don't "fix" it.

