### A-3: CTA Buttons Missing Tactile Feedback on Mobile

The `cta-primary` class has `hover:-translate-y-0.5` but no `:active` state. On mobile, the only feedback from tapping a button is the browser's default tap highlight (which is often suppressed or invisible on styled elements).

**Fix in `globals.css`:**
```css
.cta-primary {
  @apply ... hover:-translate-y-0.5 active:scale-[0.98] active:shadow-none;
}

.cta-light {
  @apply ... hover:-translate-y-0.5 active:scale-[0.98];
}

.cta-gold {
  @apply ... hover:-translate-y-0.5 active:scale-[0.98];
}

.cta-outline-dark {
  @apply ... hover:-translate-y-0.5 active:scale-[0.97];
}
```

This gives every button a subtle press-in feel on tap. Standard mobile pattern.

