## Category 6: Content Flow & Conversion Architecture

### CF-1: Page Section Order — Quote Form Too Late

Current scroll order (numbered by approximate screen on mobile):

```
1.  Hero
2.  AuthorityBar
3.  IncludedSummary
4-8.  ServiceSpread (5 services)
9-10. OfferAndIndustry
11-12. BeforeAfter
13. Testimonials
14-15. Timeline
16. About
17. ServiceArea
18-19. QuoteSection  ← Form is HERE (screen 18-19 of 21)
20. Careers
21. Footer
```

The primary conversion action (quote form) is at **screen 18 of 21**. A user who scrolls linearly passes 17 screens before reaching the form. The sticky bar mitigates this, but the page flow itself isn't optimized for conversion.

**Recommended reorder:**
```
1.  Hero (CTA: sticky bar appears after)
2.  AuthorityBar (trust)
3.  IncludedSummary (process clarity)
4-8.  ServiceSpread (services)
9-10. OfferAndIndustry (audience fit)
11. Testimonials (social proof)
12-13. BeforeAfter (visual proof)
14. QuoteSection ← MOVED UP (after proof, before "about us")
15-16. Timeline (how it works — reinforces for undecided)
17. About (brand story)
18. ServiceArea (geography)
19. Careers
20. Footer
```

**Rationale:** After seeing services (what), industries (who), testimonials (trust), and before/after (proof), the user has maximum intent. The quote form should appear at that moment. Timeline, About, ServiceArea, and Careers serve users who need more convincing — they come after the primary conversion opportunity.

**Implementation:** Reorder components in `VariantAPublicPage`:
```tsx
<main>
  <HeroSection />
  <AuthorityBar />
  <IncludedSummarySection />
  <ServiceSpreadSection />
  <OfferAndIndustrySection />
  <TestimonialSection />      {/* moved up */}
  <BeforeAfterSlider />       {/* moved up */}
  <QuoteSection />            {/* moved up */}
  <TimelineSection />         {/* moved down */}
  <AboutSection />
  <ServiceAreaSection />
  <CareersSection />
</main>
```

**Effort:** XS (5 min — just reorder JSX). **Impact: potentially significant conversion improvement.**

